<section class="vc_cta3-container" >
<div class="vc_general vc_cta3 vc_cta3-style-classic vc_cta3-shape-rounded vc_cta3-align-left vc_cta3-color-classic vc_cta3-icon-size-md vc_custom_1525880915472">
<div class="vc_cta3_content-container">
<div class="vc_cta3-content">
<header class="vc_cta3-content-header">
<h2>Context</h2>
</header>
<ul>
<li>Sustainable investments represent <strong>26%</strong> of total managed assets in the world and <strong>53%</strong> in Europe (<a href="http://www.gsi-alliance.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/GSIR_Review2016.F.pdf">2016 Global Sustainable Investment Review</a>, Global Sustainable Investment Alliance)</li>
<li>Globally sustainable investments increased by <strong>25%</strong> from 2014 to 2016 (<a href="http://www.gsi-alliance.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/GSIR_Review2016.F.pdf">2016 Global Sustainable Investment Review</a>, Global Sustainable Investment Alliance)</li>
<li><strong>78%</strong> of Millennial investors are currently investing in socially responsible or impact funds – or plan to do so in the future (<a href="https://info.swellinvesting.com/resources/money-meets-morals-study-data">Money Meets Morals Study</a>, Swell Investing 2017)</li>
<li>Among 2200 empirical studies, <strong>90%</strong> find a neutral or positive relation between Environment, Social and Governance criteria and corporate financial performance (<a href="http://www.sustainablefinance.ch/upload/cms/user/201512_JSustFinance_MetastudyPerformance.pdf">Journal of Sustainable Finance & Investment</a>)</li>
</ul></div>
</p></div>
</p></div>
</section>
</div>
</div>
</div>
